cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a new architecture for Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) to address the problem of mode collapse. The paper focuses on image generation tasks and performs experiments on synthetic and real datasets. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also introduces a new objective function and discusses its effectiveness on image-to-image translation and unsupervised feature representation tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of multiple generators and one discriminator in the proposed architecture also suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.GR (Graphics).
